{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017VBYJom4Ys4mFs37FUNhEP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Self-Evolution System Implementation Plan\n     2→\n     3→> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n     4→\n     5→**Goal:** Implement a daemon-side post-run evolution pipeline that analyzes workflow history to automatically improve prompts, add validation steps, and refine workflows.\n     6→\n     7→**Architecture:** Multi-stage LLM pipeline (Collector → Classifier → Reflector → Executor branches) running in the daemon after each workflow completion. Three executor branches: Prompt Curator (ACE-style), Script Generator (LLM code gen), DSL Mutator (deterministic Go). Changes auto-applied with JSONL audit trail and snapshots.\n     8→\n     9→**Tech Stack:** Go, SQLite, gRPC, TOML config (`github.com/BurntSushi/toml`), existing LLM agent invocation pattern.\n    10→\n    11→**Design doc:** `docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`\n    12→\n    13→---\n    14→\n    15→## Task 1: Extend Domain Types\n    16→\n    17→**Files:**\n    18→- Modify: `internal/domain/run.go`\n    19→- Modify: `internal/domain/workflow.go`\n    20→- Test: `internal/domain/run_test.go`\n    21→\n    22→**Step 1: Write failing test for Run.ProjectDir**\n    23→\n    24→Add to `internal/domain/run_test.go`:\n    25→\n    26→```go\n    27→func TestRunProjectDir(t *testing.T) {\n    28→\tr := NewRun(\"test-1\", \"develop\")\n    29→\tr.ProjectDir = \"/home/user/project\"\n    30→\tassert.Equal(t, \"/home/user/project\", r.ProjectDir)\n    31→}\n    32→```\n    33→\n    34→**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n    35→\n    36→Run: `go test ./internal/domain/ -run TestRunProjectDir -v`\n    37→Expected: FAIL — `r.ProjectDir undefined`\n    38→\n    39→**Step 3: Add ProjectDir to Run**\n    40→\n    41→In `internal/domain/run.go`, add `ProjectDir string` to the `Run` struct.\n    42→\