{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UFM7x9ZkEjoc1a9sz8V73a","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a complete picture. Let me prepare the final report.\n\n## Search Results Summary\n\nI've completed a comprehensive search of the evolution, curator, orchestrator, and collector components in the codebase. Here are my findings:\n\n### 1. Files Under `internal/evolution/`\n\nAll files exist and are production-ready:\n\n**Core Components:**\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/collector.go` (92 lines) — Gathers runs, captures, knowledge base, prompts, and workflow for evolution analysis\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go` (91 lines) — Merges lessons into prompt files using ACE-style curation\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go` (213 lines) — Wires all evolution pipeline stages together\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/classifier.go` (51 lines) — Categorizes run prompts into bug/feedback/feature/enhancement/chore\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/reflector.go` (117 lines) — Examines execution traces and extracts structured lessons\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/scriptgen.go` (73 lines) — Generates new checker/linter scripts via LLM\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go` (114 lines) — Records evolution actions and manages snapshots/knowledge base\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger.go` (64 lines) — Debounces evolution pipeline runs per project+workflow\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/llmclient.go` (13 lines) — LLMClient interface for abstraction\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go` (57 lines) — Core domain types (CollectedData, Lesson, EvolutionResult, Change)\n\n**Test Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/evolution_test.go` (21 KB)\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/corruption_test.go` (29 KB) — **UNTRACKED FILE** (shows in git status as ??)\n\n### 2. Untracked File: `corruption_test.go`\n\nThe file `/workspace/internal/evolution/corruption_test.go` is a NEW test file (29 KB) that was just added. It contains comprehensive test coverage for:\n\n**Test Categories:**\n- **Curator Corruption Scenarios** (lines 100-285):\n  - `TestCuratorCorruption_ConversationalMetaTextNoFences` — LLM returns conversational text without code fences\n  - `TestCuratorCorruption_ResponseShorterThanOriginal` — Content loss when response is shorter than original\n  - `TestCuratorCorruption_EmptyResponse` — Complete content destruction\n  - `TestCuratorCorruption_EmptyCodeFences` — Fences with no content between them\n  - `TestCuratorCorruption_RaceConcurrentApply` — Race conditions with concurrent Apply calls (10 goroutines)\n  - `TestStripCodeFences_*` — Unit tests for fence stripping logic\n\n- **Orchestrator Edge Cases** (lines 287-462):\n  - `TestOrchestratorReflectorProducesDuplicateLessons` — Handling duplicate lessons already in KB\n  - `TestOrchestratorHandleNewStepAlreadyExists` — Step name collision handling\n  - `TestOrchestratorWorkflowValidAfterMultipleEvolutionCycles` — Stability across evolution cycles\n  - `TestOrchestratorErrorInOneLessonDoesNotPreventOthers` — Error isolation between lessons\n\n- **Collector Tests** (lines 567-677):\n  - `TestCollectorWithEvolutionStoreMock` — Collector with mocked stores\n  - `TestCollectorListRunsSinceCalledWithCorrectRunID` — Run ID tracking\n  - `TestCollectorListRunsSinceEmptyWhenNoLastEvolution` — Empty sinceRunID behavior\n  - `TestCollectorWithCaptureStoreMock` — Capture store integration\n\n- **Integration Tests** (lines 679-834):\n  - `TestIntegration_CorruptPromptDetectedAndFixed` — Full cycle corruption detection/fix\n  - `TestIntegration_StabilityNoCyclesNoDrift` — 5-cycle stability test (no unwanted changes)\n  - `TestIntegration_FullCycleWithStores` — End-to-end with actual store mocks\n\nThe test file also includes mock implementations for LLM clients (errLLM, callTrackingLLM) and stores (mockEvolutionStore, mockCaptureStore).\n\n### 3. Documentation Files Mentioning Evolution/Curator/Orchestrator/Collector\n\n**Core Design & Implementation:**\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md` — Comprehensive architecture document covering the multi-stage pipeline, data collection, curator ACE principles, mutation strategies, and audit logging\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md` (2,052 lines) — Detailed task-by-task implementation plan with code examples for all components\n\n**Related Documentation:**\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`\n\n### 4. Architecture Overview\n\nThe evolution pipeline follows this flow:\n\n```\nWorkflow Run → Collector → Classifier → Reflector → Three Branches:\n                                                     ├─ Curator (prompt_improvement)\n                                                     ├─ ScriptGenerator (new_step scripts)\n                                                     └─ Mutator (workflow DSL changes)\n                                                     → Audit Logger\n```\n\n**Key Design Principles:**\n- Multi-stage LLM pipeline for analysis and content generation\n- Deterministic Go code for structural manipulation (DSL, file I/O)\n- Project+workflow scoping for multi-project support\n- ACE-style (Agentic Context Engineering) prompt evolution as structured lessons\n- JSONL audit trail with file snapshots before changes\n- Knowledge base accumulation per workflow\n- Error isolation: one lesson failure doesn't stop others"},{"typ